## Example 2
<instruction>
Implement a C program that performs the bubble sort algorithm on an array of integers. The program should define and call a function `bubbleSort` to sort the array in ascending order. Also, implement another function `printArray` to print the elements of the array before and after sorting.
</instruction>

<response>
#include <stdio.h>

void printArray(int arr[], int size) {
    for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
        printf("%d ", arr[i]);
    }
    printf("\n");
}

void bubbleSort(int arr[], int size) {
    for (int i = 0; i < size - 1; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < size - i - 1; j++) {
            if (arr[j] > arr[j + 1]) {
                int temp = arr[j];
                arr[j] = arr[j + 1];
                arr[j + 1] = temp;
            }
        }
    }
}

int main() {
    int arr[] = {64, 34, 25, 12, 22, 11, 90};
    int n = sizeof(arr) / sizeof(arr[0]);

    printf("Unsorted array: ");
    printArray(arr, n);

    bubbleSort(arr, n);

    printf("Sorted array: ");
    printArray(arr, n);

    return 0;
}
</response>

<tests>
1. Input: `{64, 34, 25, 12, 22, 11, 90}`
   Output:
   ```
   Unsorted array: 64 34 25 12 22 11 90
   Sorted array: 11 12 22 25 34 64 90
   ```
2. Input: `{5, 2, 9, 1, 5, 6}`
   Output:
   ```
   Unsorted array: 5 2 9 1 5 6
   Sorted array: 1 2 5 5 6 9
   ```
</tests>

